spec: concurrent_futures_extra54
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(concurrent.futures)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html#concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor — ThreadPoolExecutor documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html#concurrent.futures.Future — Future documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends concurrent_futures_extra53.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __name__/__module__/__qualname__, CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor/InvalidStateError identity and bases, as_completed/wait __name__/__qualname__, FIRST_COMPLETED/FIRST_EXCEPTION/ALL_COMPLETED values and __len__(), class __module__/__name__/__len__() tables, submit/shutdown qualname lens, Future method qualname lens, class __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ tables, wait/__name__=='wait', as_completed/__name__=='as_completed', wait/__qualname__.__len__()==4, as_completed/__qualname__.__len__()==12 (extra51), class __class__.__name__/__qualname__ equality (extra44/extra45), wait/__class__.__module__=='builtins' and ThreadPoolExecutor/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra45), class __doc__/__class__.__module__=='builtins' tables (extra47/extra49), ProcessPoolExecutor/Future/Executor __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') (extra52), as_completed/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') (extra52), ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future __init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') (extra52), class __repr__.__class__.__name__ tables (extra53), class __weakref__.__class__.__name__ tables (extra53), exception __repr__.__class__.__name__ tables (extra53)."
    - "This spec covers (cfall54 namespace): concurrent.futures.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('list') — cf.__all__ is a plain Python list (14 items); __class__.__name__ == 'list'; __eq__('list') returns True. concurrent.futures.__all__.__len__()==14 cross-check via table. ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future __eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') — these pure-Python cf classes do not define custom __eq__; they inherit object.__eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper. CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor __eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') — exception classes inherit __eq__ from BaseException (C type) chain; object.__eq__ is a C-level slot wrapper. No prior concurrent.futures spec has captured __all__.__class__.__name__ equality, __all__.__len__() equality, or __eq__.__class__.__name__ as string equality checks."
    - "concurrent.futures.__all__.__class__.__name__ == 'list'. The concurrent.futures module exposes __all__ as a plain Python list of 14 exported names: ['FIRST_COMPLETED', 'FIRST_EXCEPTION', 'ALL_COMPLETED', 'CancelledError', 'TimeoutError', 'InvalidStateError', 'BrokenExecutor', 'Future', 'Executor', 'wait', 'as_completed', 'ProcessPoolExecutor', 'ThreadPoolExecutor', 'InterpreterPoolExecutor']. list is a built-in type; __class__.__name__ == 'list'. No prior concurrent.futures spec captured __all__.__class__.__name__ as a string equality check. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.__all__.__len__() == 14. The __all__ list contains 14 entries. This is a cross-check of the cardinality fact. No prior concurrent.futures spec captured __all__.__len__() as an equality (only __len__()==14 as a length-only fact in earlier metadata specs). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ThreadPoolExecutor is a pure-Python class in Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py. It does not define __eq__; it inherits object.__eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). No prior concurrent.futures spec captured __eq__.__class__.__name__ as a string equality check. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ProcessPoolExecutor is a pure-Python class in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py. It inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.Future.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Future is a pure-Python class in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py. It does not define __eq__; it inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.CancelledError.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. CancelledError is a subclass of BaseException (C type). Exception classes in the BaseException chain inherit object.__eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). CancelledError defines no custom __eq__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.TimeoutError.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. TimeoutError is a subclass of OSError → Exception → BaseException. It inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. BrokenExecutor is a subclass of RuntimeError → Exception → BaseException. It inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures.__all__ container type and length — extra54
#
# concurrent.futures.__all__ is a plain Python list of 14 exported names.
# The list type is a built-in type; __class__.__name__ == 'list'.
# __all__.__len__() == 14.
#
# No prior concurrent.futures spec has captured __all__.__class__.__name__
# as a string equality check. Extra54 introduces this in the cfall54 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra54.all_metadata_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.__all__ type and length in cfall54 namespace — __all__ is a plain Python list (14 items); __class__.__name__.__eq__('list') returns True; __len__() == 14; no prior cf spec captured __all__.__class__.__name__ equality"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: cfall54allmeta

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [all_is_list, concurrent.futures.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["list"], true, "concurrent.futures.__all__.__class__.__name__ == 'list' — cf.__all__ is a plain Python list of 14 exported names; list is a built-in type; __class__.__name__ == 'list'; first __all__.__class__.__name__ equality check in any concurrent.futures spec"]
    - [all_len,     concurrent.futures.__all__.__len__,                   [],       14,   "concurrent.futures.__all__.__len__() == 14 — __all__ contains 14 entries: FIRST_COMPLETED, FIRST_EXCEPTION, ALL_COMPLETED, CancelledError, TimeoutError, InvalidStateError, BrokenExecutor, Future, Executor, wait, as_completed, ProcessPoolExecutor, ThreadPoolExecutor, InterpreterPoolExecutor"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future
# __eq__.__class__.__name__ — extra54
#
# ThreadPoolExecutor, ProcessPoolExecutor, and Future are pure-Python classes
# in Lib/concurrent/futures/. None of them define a custom __eq__ method.
# They inherit object.__eq__, which is a C-level slot wrapper:
#   ThreadPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__  == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#   ProcessPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#   Future.__eq__.__class__.__name__              == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#
# No prior concurrent.futures spec has captured __eq__.__class__.__name__
# as a string equality check. Extra54 introduces this in the cfall54 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra54.executor_future_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures ThreadPoolExecutor/ProcessPoolExecutor/Future __eq__.__class__.__name__ in cfall54 namespace — pure-Python cf classes inherit object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'; no prior cf spec captured __eq__.__class__.__name__ as string equality"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: cfall54execeqname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ThreadPoolExecutor,  ThreadPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,  ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ThreadPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ThreadPoolExecutor inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__; first __eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any concurrent.futures spec"]
    - [ProcessPoolExecutor, ProcessPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ProcessPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ProcessPoolExecutor inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__"]
    - [Future,              Future.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,              ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "Future.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — Future is a pure-Python class in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py; inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# concurrent.futures CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor
# __eq__.__class__.__name__ — extra54
#
# CancelledError, TimeoutError, and BrokenExecutor are exception classes that
# inherit (directly or indirectly) from BaseException. None of them define a
# custom __eq__ method. They inherit object.__eq__ via the BaseException chain,
# which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor):
#   CancelledError.__eq__.__class__.__name__  == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#   TimeoutError.__eq__.__class__.__name__    == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#   BrokenExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__  == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#
# No prior concurrent.futures spec has captured exception __eq__.__class__.__name__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table concurrent_futures_extra54.exception_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures CancelledError/TimeoutError/BrokenExecutor __eq__.__class__.__name__ in cfall54 namespace — exception classes inherit object.__eq__ via BaseException chain (C-level slot wrapper); __eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'; no prior cf spec captured exception __eq__.__class__.__name__"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: cfall54exceqname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [CancelledError, CancelledError.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "CancelledError.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — CancelledError inherits object.__eq__ via BaseException chain (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__; first exception __eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any concurrent.futures spec"]
    - [TimeoutError,   TimeoutError.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,   ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "TimeoutError.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — TimeoutError subclasses OSError → Exception → BaseException; inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__"]
    - [BrokenExecutor, BrokenExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "BrokenExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — BrokenExecutor subclasses RuntimeError → Exception → BaseException; inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra54
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant concurrent_futures_extra54.all_class_name_list_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.__all__.__class__.__name__ == 'list' — cf.__all__ is a plain Python list of 14 exported names; list is a built-in type; __class__.__name__ == 'list'; first __all__.__class__.__name__ equality check in any concurrent.futures spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: concurrent.futures.__all__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["list"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra54.ThreadPoolExecutor_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ThreadPoolExecutor inherits object.__eq__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); defines no custom __eq__; first __eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any concurrent.futures spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ThreadPoolExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra54.Future_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — Future is a pure-Python class in Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py; inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__; novel __eq__.__class__.__name__ check for Future"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Future.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra54.CancelledError_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.CancelledError.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — CancelledError inherits object.__eq__ via BaseException chain (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__; first exception __eq__.__class__.__name__ check in any concurrent.futures spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: CancelledError.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant concurrent_futures_extra54.BrokenExecutor_eq_class_name_eq:
  description: "concurrent.futures.BrokenExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — BrokenExecutor subclasses RuntimeError → Exception → BaseException; inherits object.__eq__ (C-level slot wrapper); defines no custom __eq__"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: BrokenExecutor.__eq__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true
